<heading>health - Diagnose node health.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>
<pre>
  health
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Scans the entire node tree and displays the structural health status
for every node. Each node is checked for a readable <code>yak.yml</code>,
a registered executor, and an existing <code>app.py</code> entry point.
No Python modules are loaded — validation is purely structural.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Icons
</heading>

<pre>
  ✓   healthy
  ⚠   degraded
  ✗   unhealthy
</pre>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
<code>info</code> — show detailed node information.
</paragraph>
